<main>
  <p>An API that converts a given calendar date to its affiliated timestamp and vice versa.</p>
  <p>View the <a href="https://github.com/autumnchris/timestamp-api" target="_blank">source code</a> for this project.</p>
  <hr>
  <section>
    <h2>Example Usages</h2>
    <div class="subsection">
      <h3>Get the Current Date</h3>
      <p>To get the data for the current date, go to the route:</p>
      <pre><code>/api/timestamp</code></pre>
    </div>
    <div class="subsection">
      <h3>Get Other Dates</h3>
      <p>To get the data for a specific date, add a parameter of a natural language date or a unix timestamp to the set route. Natural language dates must be written in <code>YYYY-MM-DD</code> formatting such as:</p>
      <pre><code>/api/timestamp/2018-10-31</code></pre>
      <p>Unix timestamps must be a valid set of numbers such as:</p>
      <pre><code>/api/timestamp/1540944000000</code></pre>
    <div>
  </section>
  <section>
    <h2>Example Output</h2>
    <p>A successful output should return a unix timestamp and its associated UTC date.</p>
    <pre><samp>{
"unix": 1540944000000,
"utc": "Wed, 31 Oct 2018 00:00:00 GMT"
}</samp></pre>
  </section>
</main>
